Responsibilities : 
Functional Title Infrastructure Engineer, Systems Engineer ( Storage and Backup Administrator) 
Storage and Backup Administrator
 Perform Storage and Backup administration activities as part of the Firm?s Technical Infrastructure team. 
Provide day to day operational support of storage and backup environments: EMC Networker, EMC Data Domain, EMC VNX and VMAX, Hitachi HDS 
Monitor ticket queue and email to identify and resolve production issues 
Monitor disk and tape backup environment to make sure backups complete successfully 
Manage configuration of disk and tape backup, including tape labeling, pool management, and schedule management 
Take ownership of issues to see them through to resolution 
Provide client support related to storage and backup environments via email and phone, escalating as necessary 
Work with global team, taking and providing warm handover to ensure continuity of coverage 
Work with platform vendors to pursue issue resolution 
Potential cross training with other platforms: Unix, Windows, Database 
Independent and comfortable in a fast pace and constantly changing environment 
Analytical and have the ability to apply your skills and experience to create client-oriented solutions 
Requirements : 
Familiarity with Unix/Linux command line operations and server support 
Understanding of how to troubleshoot basic Unix/Linux problems 
Experience in medium to large IT infrastructure across multiple datacenters 
Good understanding of enterprise level change, incident, and problem management processes 
Effective communication, analytical, and troubleshooting skills 
Good interpersonal skills and ability to work well on a global team 
Ability to work and prioritize in a highly dynamic work environment with a global focus 
Automation utilizing scripting languages like bash, Python and/or Perl 
Demonstrable experience supporting one or both of the following in a large environment: EMC Networker, EMC Data Domain, EMC Avamar 
Tape backup data restore using EMC Networker 
Familiarity with AutoSys is a plus 
Familiarity with SRDF and SRDF/A technologies is a plus 
